CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 29, 1958, pg. 6, reads: "'Main Street's' Four - Homewood Ave., the 'Main Street' which dissects the Homewood area, has several liquor dispensing establishments, including... (top right picture): The White Hawk Cafe in the 700 block... - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: North Homewood Avenue at Fleury Way with Imperial Paint and Appliances store, White Hawk Cafe, and G. C. Murphy department store, Homewood
